{"meta":{"updateDate":1691007959623,"pPcc":"SAT#Q","questionId":"96a45430","skill_cd":"Q.B.","score_band_range_cd":5,"skill_desc":"Percentages","createDate":1691007959623,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Problem-Solving and Data Analysis","ibn":"028999-DC","external_id":null,"primary_class_cd":"Q","uId":"8ece062f-1d2d-4d01-8b21-f27bdd0920d3","difficulty":"M"},"source":"legacy","detail":{"item_id":"028999-DC","section":"Math","prompt":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">A number <em class=\"inline_variable \">n</em> is increased 6%. If the result is 318, what is the value of <em class=\"inline_variable \">n</em> ?</p>\n","answer":{"style":"Multiple Choice","choices":{"a":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">199</p>\n"},"b":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">299</p>\n"},"c":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">300</p>\n"},"d":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">337</p>\n"}},"correct_choice":"c","rationale":"<p>Choice C is correct. The decimal equivalent of 6% is 0.06. Since increasing the number <span class=\"italic\">n</span> by 6% yields the number 318, this situation can be represented by the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"n  times, open parenthesis, 1 plus 0 point 0 6, close parenthesis, equals 318\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"n times 1 point 0 6, equals 318\"></span>. Dividing both sides of this equation by 1.06 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"n equals 300\"></span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the result when <span class=\"italic\">n</span> is increased by 60%, not by 6%. Choice B is incorrect. This is the approximate result of decreasing 318 by 6%. Choice D is incorrect. This is the approximate result of increasing 318 by 6%.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n"}}}